OL,3,CHow algae on our railways could
OL,4,Ccapture 400x more carbon than trees
OL,6,FAlgacraft is investigating the
OL,7,Findustrial production of algae and its
OL,8,Fuses. It approached London North
OL,9,FEastern Railway (LNER) for help with
OL,10,Fthe project.
OL,12,F"We thought it was an absolutely
OL,13,Ffantastic idea." said Olivia Mouter,
OL,14,FEnvironmental Partnership Manager,
OL,15,FLNER. "We do have these brownfield,
OL,16,Fdead spaces across our network and we
OL,17,Fthought what a wonderful idea to put
OL,18,Fuse to that land and make it into
OL,19,Fsomething that is really beneficial to
OL,20,Fthe company and really beneficial
OL,21,Fenvironmentally as well."
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G2/6
