OL,3,CHow algae on our railways could
OL,4,Ccapture 400x more carbon than trees
OL,6,FDr Ravasz added: "This is a sixty
OL,7,Flitre test site, it's comparable to a
OL,8,Fhandful of potted plants for carbon
OL,9,Fcapture.
OL,11,F"So we need to upscale it by a
OL,12,Fconsiderable amount and then it will
OL,13,Fbe one of the methods to capture
OL,14,Fcarbon and help reduce our carbon
OL,15,Ffootprint as a whole."
OL,17,FOnce harvested the algae can be used
OL,18,Fas fertiliser in the local area. Other
OL,19,Fuses, such as producing bio plastics,
OL,20,Fare being explored.
